Note:
Runa Standard Library: C++ Interoperability

This module provides advanced C++ integration that surpasses traditional language 
interop solutions by providing deep C++ ecosystem integration, automatic binding
generation, and modern C++ feature support.

Revolutionary Features:
- Automatic header parsing and binding generation from C++ headers
- Template metaprogramming bridge with Runa generic system
- RAII integration with automatic resource management
- Exception handling bridge (C++ exceptions ↔ Runa errors)
- STL container zero-copy integration (vector, map, etc.)
- Modern C++ features: constexpr, concepts, coroutines (C++20)
- Compiler integration: GCC, Clang, MSVC with optimization flags
- CMake integration for automatic build configuration
- Memory model bridging (stack/heap allocation coordination)
- Virtual function and inheritance support
- Template specialization and SFINAE compatibility
- Automatic ABI compatibility detection and adaptation
- Compile-time C++ evaluation integration

Technical Superiority:
- Direct memory sharing with C++ objects (no marshalling overhead)
- Automatic lifetime management bridging RAII with Runa GC
- Template instantiation on-demand from Runa generic calls
- Exception stack unwinding across language boundaries
- Optimized calling conventions for maximum performance
- Advanced type deduction and perfect forwarding support
:End Note

Import "interop/ffi" as ffi
Import "collections/dict" as dict_utils
Import "collections/list" as list_utils
Import "string/format" as string_utils
Import "errors/errors" as error_utils
Import "concurrent/locks" as locks
Import "memory/core" as memory_utils
Import "json/json" as json_utils
Import "uuid/uuid" as uuid_utils

Note: C++ Interop Types
Type CppRuntime is Dictionary with:
    runtime_id as String
    compiler_type as CppCompilerType
    compiler_version as String
    standard_version as CppStandardVersion
    compilation_flags as List[String]
    include_paths as List[String]
    library_paths as List[String]
    loaded_libraries as Dictionary[String, CppLibrary]
    header_cache as Dictionary[String, CppHeader]
    template_cache as Dictionary[String, CppTemplateInstance]
    exception_handler as CppExceptionHandler
    memory_manager as CppMemoryManager
    performance_metrics as CppPerformanceMetrics
    created_at as Float

Type CppCompilerType is:
    | GCC | Clang | MSVC | Intel | Custom with name as String

Type CppStandardVersion is:
    | Cpp98 | Cpp03 | Cpp11 | Cpp14 | Cpp17 | Cpp20 | Cpp23

Type CppLibrary is Dictionary with:
    library_id as String
    library_name as String
    library_path as String
    header_files as List[String]
    compiled_objects as Dictionary[String, CppCompiledObject]
    exported_symbols as Dictionary[String, CppSymbol]
    dependencies as List[String]
    abi_version as String
    compilation_metadata as CppCompilationMetadata
    reference_count as Integer

Type CppCompiledObject is Dictionary with:
    object_id as String
    object_file_path as String
    source_files as List[String]
    symbol_table as Dictionary[String, CppSymbol]
    debug_info as Optional[CppDebugInfo]
    optimization_level as CppOptimizationLevel

Type CppOptimizationLevel is:
    | Debug | Release | OptimizeSize | OptimizeSpeed | Custom with flags as List[String]

Type CppSymbol is Dictionary with:
    symbol_id as String
    mangled_name as String
    demangled_name as String
    symbol_type as CppSymbolType
    address as Integer
    size as Integer
    linkage as CppLinkage
    visibility as CppVisibility
    signature as Optional[CppSignature]

Type CppSymbolType is:
    | Function | Variable | Class | Namespace | Template | TypeAlias | Enum

Type CppLinkage is:
    | ExternalLinkage | InternalLinkage | NoLinkage

Type CppVisibility is:
    | Public | Protected | Private | Default

Type CppSignature is Dictionary with:
    return_type as CppType
    parameters as List[CppParameter]
    template_parameters as List[CppTemplateParameter]
    exception_specification as CppExceptionSpecification
    calling_convention as CppCallingConvention
    cv_qualifiers as CppCVQualifiers
    ref_qualifier as Optional[CppRefQualifier]

Type CppParameter is Dictionary with:
    name as String
    cpp_type as CppType
    default_value as Optional[CppExpression]
    is_variadic as Boolean

Type CppType is:
    | Void | Bool | Char | SignedChar | UnsignedChar
    | Short | UnsignedShort | Int | UnsignedInt
    | Long | UnsignedLong | LongLong | UnsignedLongLong
    | Float | Double | LongDouble
    | Pointer with pointee_type as CppType
    | Reference with referenced_type as CppType
    | RValueReference with referenced_type as CppType
    | Array with element_type as CppType and size as Optional[CppExpression]
    | Function with signature as CppSignature
    | Class with class_name as String and template_args as List[CppTemplateArgument]
    | Enum with enum_name as String and underlying_type as Optional[CppType]
    | Template with template_name as String and parameters as List[CppTemplateParameter]
    | Auto | Decltype with expression as CppExpression
    | Qualified with qualifiers as CppCVQualifiers and base_type as CppType

Type CppCVQualifiers is Dictionary with:
    is_const as Boolean
    is_volatile as Boolean
    is_mutable as Boolean

Type CppRefQualifier is:
    | LValueRef | RValueRef

Type CppExceptionSpecification is:
    | NoThrow | DynamicThrow with types as List[CppType]
    | NoExceptSpecification with condition as Optional[CppExpression]

Type CppCallingConvention is:
    | Cdecl | Stdcall | Fastcall | Thiscall | Vectorcall

Type CppTemplateParameter is Dictionary with:
    parameter_name as String
    parameter_kind as CppTemplateParameterKind
    default_argument as Optional[CppTemplateArgument]
    constraints as List[CppConcept]

Type CppTemplateParameterKind is:
    | TypeParameter | NonTypeParameter with type as CppType
    | TemplateTemplateParameter with parameters as List[CppTemplateParameter]

Type CppTemplateArgument is:
    | TypeArgument with type as CppType
    | ValueArgument with value as CppExpression
    | TemplateArgument with template_name as String

Type CppConcept is Dictionary with:
    concept_name as String
    requirements as List[CppRequirement]
    template_parameters as List[CppTemplateParameter]

Type CppRequirement is Dictionary with:
    requirement_type as CppRequirementType
    expression as CppExpression
    description as String

Type CppRequirementType is:
    | SimpleRequirement | TypeRequirement | CompoundRequirement | NestedRequirement

Type CppExpression is Dictionary with:
    expression_type as CppExpressionType
    value as Any
    type_info as Optional[CppType]
    is_constexpr as Boolean

Type CppExpressionType is:
    | Literal | Identifier | BinaryOperation | UnaryOperation | FunctionCall
    | MemberAccess | ArraySubscript | ConditionalExpression | LambdaExpression

Type CppHeader is Dictionary with:
    header_id as String
    header_path as String
    include_guard as Optional[String]
    includes as List[String]
    declarations as List[CppDeclaration]
    macros as Dictionary[String, CppMacro]
    namespaces as Dictionary[String, CppNamespace]
    parsed_timestamp as Float
    checksum as String

Type CppDeclaration is Dictionary with:
    declaration_id as String
    declaration_type as CppDeclarationType
    name as String
    location as CppSourceLocation
    access_specifier as CppVisibility
    attributes as List[CppAttribute]

Type CppDeclarationType is:
    | FunctionDeclaration | VariableDeclaration | ClassDeclaration
    | NamespaceDeclaration | TemplateDeclaration | UsingDeclaration

Type CppSourceLocation is Dictionary with:
    file_path as String
    line_number as Integer
    column_number as Integer

Type CppAttribute is Dictionary with:
    attribute_name as String
    arguments as List[CppExpression]

Type CppMacro is Dictionary with:
    macro_name as String
    parameters as List[String]
    body as String
    is_function_like as Boolean

Type CppNamespace is Dictionary with:
    namespace_name as String
    nested_namespaces as Dictionary[String, CppNamespace]
    declarations as List[CppDeclaration]
    using_directives as List[String]

Type CppTemplateInstance is Dictionary with:
    instance_id as String
    template_name as String
    template_arguments as List[CppTemplateArgument]
    instantiated_type as Optional[CppType]
    instantiated_function as Optional[CppFunction]
    compilation_status as CppCompilationStatus
    binary_code as Optional[List[Integer]]

Type CppCompilationStatus is:
    | Pending | Compiling | Compiled | Failed

Type CppFunction is Dictionary with:
    function_id as String
    function_name as String
    mangled_name as String
    signature as CppSignature
    is_template as Boolean
    is_virtual as Boolean
    is_pure_virtual as Boolean
    is_constructor as Boolean
    is_destructor as Boolean
    is_operator as Boolean
    overload_index as Integer
    class_context as Optional[String]
    call_count as Integer
    total_execution_time as Float

Type CppClass is Dictionary with:
    class_id as String
    class_name as String
    full_qualified_name as String
    base_classes as List[CppInheritance]
    member_functions as Dictionary[String, CppFunction]
    member_variables as Dictionary[String, CppVariable]
    constructors as List[CppFunction]
    destructor as Optional[CppFunction]
    virtual_table as Optional[CppVirtualTable]
    template_specializations as List[CppTemplateInstance]
    size_bytes as Integer
    alignment as Integer

Type CppInheritance is Dictionary with:
    base_class_name as String
    inheritance_type as CppInheritanceType
    access_specifier as CppVisibility
    is_virtual as Boolean

Type CppInheritanceType is:
    | PublicInheritance | ProtectedInheritance | PrivateInheritance

Type CppVariable is Dictionary with:
    variable_id as String
    variable_name as String
    variable_type as CppType
    is_static as Boolean
    is_const as Boolean
    is_mutable as Boolean
    offset as Optional[Integer]
    default_value as Optional[CppExpression]

Type CppVirtualTable is Dictionary with:
    vtable_id as String
    virtual_functions as List[CppFunction]
    vtable_address as Integer
    entry_count as Integer

Type CppExceptionHandler is Dictionary with:
    handler_id as String
    active_handlers as Dictionary[String, CppExceptionInfo]
    exception_mapping as Dictionary[String, String]
    unwinding_enabled as Boolean

Type CppExceptionInfo is Dictionary with:
    exception_type as String
    exception_object as Integer
    stack_trace as List[CppStackFrame]
    what_message as String
    runa_equivalent as Optional[String]

Type CppStackFrame is Dictionary with:
    frame_id as String
    function_name as String
    source_location as CppSourceLocation
    local_variables as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CppMemoryManager is Dictionary with:
    manager_id as String
    heap_allocators as Dictionary[String, CppAllocator]
    stack_regions as List[CppStackRegion]
    shared_objects as Dictionary[String, CppSharedObject]
    raii_objects as Dictionary[String, CppRAIIObject]
    memory_pools as List[CppMemoryPool]

Type CppAllocator is Dictionary with:
    allocator_id as String
    allocator_type as CppAllocatorType
    total_allocated as Integer
    peak_allocated as Integer
    allocation_count as Integer
    fragmentation_ratio as Float

Type CppAllocatorType is:
    | StandardAllocator | PoolAllocator | StackAllocator | CustomAllocator with name as String

Type CppStackRegion is Dictionary with:
    region_id as String
    base_address as Integer
    size_bytes as Integer
    current_offset as Integer
    owner_thread as String

Type CppSharedObject is Dictionary with:
    object_id as String
    cpp_object_address as Integer
    runa_reference as Any
    reference_count as Integer
    destructor_function as Optional[String]
    cleanup_handlers as List[String]

Type CppRAIIObject is Dictionary with:
    raii_id as String
    cpp_object as Integer
    destructor as String
    cleanup_order as Integer
    scope_level as Integer

Type CppMemoryPool is Dictionary with:
    pool_id as String
    block_size as Integer
    block_count as Integer
    free_blocks as Integer
    base_address as Integer

Type CppCompilationMetadata is Dictionary with:
    compiler_command as String
    compilation_time_ms as Integer
    object_file_size as Integer
    debug_symbols_included as Boolean
    optimization_flags as List[String]
    preprocessor_defines as Dictionary[String, String]
    linked_libraries as List[String]

Type CppDebugInfo is Dictionary with:
    debug_format as CppDebugFormat
    symbol_table as Dictionary[String, CppSymbol]
    line_number_table as Dictionary[Integer, CppSourceLocation]
    type_information as Dictionary[String, CppType]

Type CppDebugFormat is:
    | DWARF | PDB | COFF | STABS

Type CppPerformanceMetrics is Dictionary with:
    total_function_calls as Integer
    total_compilation_time_ms as Integer
    cache_hit_rate as Float
    template_instantiation_count as Integer
    exception_count as Integer
    memory_allocations as Integer
    average_call_time_ns as Float

Type CppResult[T] is:
    | CppSuccess with value as T and metrics as CppCallMetrics
    | CppError with error as CppException and partial_result as Optional[T]

Type CppCallMetrics is Dictionary with:
    call_duration_ns as Integer
    memory_allocated as Integer
    memory_freed as Integer
    exceptions_thrown as Integer
    template_instantiations as Integer

Type CppException is Dictionary with:
    exception_id as String
    exception_type as String
    what_message as String
    source_location as CppSourceLocation
    stack_trace as List[CppStackFrame]
    nested_exception as Optional[CppException]

Note: Global C++ Runtime State
Let global_cpp_runtime be None as Optional[CppRuntime]
Let global_cpp_lock be locks.create_reentrant_lock
Let cpp_compilation_cache be dict_utils.create_empty_dict
Let cpp_template_cache be dict_utils.create_empty_dict

Note: C++ Runtime Initialization
Process initialize_cpp_runtime that takes config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns CppResult[CppRuntime]:
    Try:
        locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_cpp_lock
        
        If global_cpp_runtime is not equal to None:
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_cpp_lock
            Return CppSuccess with:
                value as global_cpp_runtime
                metrics as create_empty_cpp_metrics
        
        Let compiler_type be parse_compiler_type with:
            type_str as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as config and key as "compiler" and default as "gcc"
        
        Let standard_version be parse_standard_version with:
            version_str as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as config and key as "standard" and default as "c++17"
        
        Note: Verify compiler availability
        Let compiler_check = verify_cpp_compiler with:
            compiler as compiler_type
            standard as standard_version
        
        If not compiler_check.available:
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_cpp_lock
            Return CppError with:
                error as create_cpp_exception with type as "CompilerNotFound" and message as compiler_check.error
                partial_result as None
        
        Note: Setup compilation environment
        Let include_paths be dict_utils.get_value_or_default with:
            dict as config
            key as "include_paths"
            default as get_default_include_paths with compiler as compiler_type
        
        Let library_paths be dict_utils.get_value_or_default with:
            dict as config
            key as "library_paths"
            default as get_default_library_paths with compiler as compiler_type
        
        Let compilation_flags be dict_utils.get_value_or_default with:
            dict as config
            key as "compilation_flags"
            default as get_default_compilation_flags with standard as standard_version
        
        Note: Initialize memory manager
        Let memory_manager be create_cpp_memory_manager with config as config
        
        Note: Initialize exception handler
        Let exception_handler be create_cpp_exception_handler with config as config
        
        Let runtime be CppRuntime with:
            runtime_id as generate_cpp_runtime_id
            compiler_type as compiler_type
            compiler_version as compiler_check.version
            standard_version as standard_version
            compilation_flags as compilation_flags
            include_paths as include_paths
            library_paths as library_paths
            loaded_libraries as dict_utils.create_empty_dict
            header_cache as dict_utils.create_empty_dict
            template_cache as dict_utils.create_empty_dict
            exception_handler as exception_handler
            memory_manager as memory_manager
            performance_metrics as create_cpp_performance_metrics
            created_at as get_current_timestamp
        
        Set global_cpp_runtime to runtime
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_cpp_lock
        
        Return CppSuccess with:
            value as runtime
            metrics as create_empty_cpp_metrics
    
    Catch error:
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_cpp_lock
        Return CppError with:
            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "InitializationError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Process shutdown_cpp_runtime returns CppResult[Boolean]:
    Try:
        locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_cpp_lock
        
        If global_cpp_runtime is equal to None:
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_cpp_lock
            Return CppSuccess with value as false and metrics as create_empty_cpp_metrics
        
        Let runtime be global_cpp_runtime
        
        Note: Cleanup RAII objects in reverse order
        Let cleanup_result be cleanup_raii_objects with manager as runtime.memory_manager
        If not cleanup_result.success:
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_cpp_lock
            Return CppError with:
                error as create_cpp_exception with type as "CleanupError" and message as cleanup_result.error
                partial_result as None
        
        Note: Unload all libraries
        For each library_id in dict_utils.get_keys with dict as runtime.loaded_libraries:
            Let unload_result be unload_cpp_library with library_id as library_id
            Continue  Note: Continue even if unload fails
        
        Set global_cpp_runtime to None
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_cpp_lock
        
        Return CppSuccess with value as true and metrics as create_empty_cpp_metrics
    
    Catch error:
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_cpp_lock
        Return CppError with:
            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "ShutdownError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Note: Header Parsing and Binding Generation
Process parse_cpp_header that takes header_path as String and parsing_options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns CppResult[CppHeader]:
    Try:
        Let runtime_result be ensure_cpp_runtime_initialized
        Match runtime_result:
            When CppError:
                Return runtime_result
            When CppSuccess:
                Let runtime be runtime_result.value
                
                Note: Check header cache
                Let cache_key be calculate_header_cache_key with path as header_path and options as parsing_options
                If runtime.header_cache contains cache_key:
                    Let cached_header be runtime.header_cache[cache_key]
                    Return CppSuccess with:
                        value as cached_header
                        metrics as create_empty_cpp_metrics
                
                Note: Parse header with Clang/GCC
                Let parse_result be parse_header_with_compiler with:
                    header_path as header_path
                    compiler as runtime.compiler_type
                    include_paths as runtime.include_paths
                    standard as runtime.standard_version
                    options as parsing_options
                
                Match parse_result:
                    When CppParseFailure:
                        Return CppError with:
                            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "ParseError" and message as parse_result.error
                            partial_result as None
                    When CppParseSuccess:
                        Let header_ast be parse_result.ast
                        
                        Note: Extract declarations from AST
                        Let extraction_result be extract_declarations_from_ast with:
                            ast as header_ast
                            header_path as header_path
                        
                        Let header_id be generate_header_id with path as header_path
                        
                        Let cpp_header be CppHeader with:
                            header_id as header_id
                            header_path as header_path
                            include_guard as extraction_result.include_guard
                            includes as extraction_result.includes
                            declarations as extraction_result.declarations
                            macros as extraction_result.macros
                            namespaces as extraction_result.namespaces
                            parsed_timestamp as get_current_timestamp
                            checksum as calculate_file_checksum with path as header_path
                        
                        Set runtime.header_cache[cache_key] to cpp_header
                        
                        Return CppSuccess with:
                            value as cpp_header
                            metrics as create_empty_cpp_metrics
    
    Catch error:
        Return CppError with:
            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "UnexpectedError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Process generate_cpp_bindings that takes header as CppHeader and binding_options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns CppResult[String]:
    Try:
        Let runtime_result be ensure_cpp_runtime_initialized
        Match runtime_result:
            When CppError:
                Return runtime_result
            When CppSuccess:
                Let runtime be runtime_result.value
                
                Note: Generate binding code for each declaration
                Let binding_code_parts be list_utils.create_empty_list
                
                For each declaration in header.declarations:
                    Let binding_result be generate_declaration_binding with:
                        declaration as declaration
                        options as binding_options
                    
                    Match binding_result:
                        When CppBindingSuccess:
                            list_utils.append with list as binding_code_parts and item as binding_result.code
                        When CppBindingFailure:
                            Note: Continue with warning, don't fail entire generation
                            Continue
                
                Note: Generate header and footer
                Let header_code be generate_binding_header with:
                    header as header
                    runtime as runtime
                
                Let footer_code be generate_binding_footer with:
                    header as header
                    runtime as runtime
                
                Note: Combine all parts
                Let complete_binding_code be string_utils.join with:
                    list as list_utils.create_list_with_items with items as [
                        header_code,
                        string_utils.join with list as binding_code_parts and separator as "\n\n",
                        footer_code
                    ]
                    separator as "\n\n"
                
                Return CppSuccess with:
                    value as complete_binding_code
                    metrics as create_empty_cpp_metrics
    
    Catch error:
        Return CppError with:
            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "BindingGenerationError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Note: C++ Code Compilation and Loading
Process compile_cpp_code that takes source_code as String and compilation_config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns CppResult[CppLibrary]:
    Try:
        Let runtime_result be ensure_cpp_runtime_initialized
        Match runtime_result:
            When CppError:
                Return runtime_result
            When CppSuccess:
                Let runtime be runtime_result.value
                
                Let library_name be dict_utils.get_value_or_default with:
                    dict as compilation_config
                    key as "library_name"
                    default as generate_library_name
                
                Let optimization_level be parse_optimization_level with:
                    level_str as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as compilation_config and key as "optimization" and default as "release"
                
                Note: Create temporary source file
                Let source_file_path be create_temporary_source_file with:
                    source_code as source_code
                    file_extension as ".cpp"
                
                Note: Compile with C++ compiler
                Let compile_start_time be get_high_precision_timestamp
                Let compile_result be compile_cpp_source with:
                    source_file as source_file_path
                    output_library as library_name
                    compiler as runtime.compiler_type
                    standard as runtime.standard_version
                    optimization as optimization_level
                    include_paths as runtime.include_paths
                    library_paths as runtime.library_paths
                    additional_flags as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as compilation_config and key as "flags" and default as list_utils.create_empty_list
                
                Let compile_end_time be get_high_precision_timestamp
                Let compilation_time be compile_end_time minus compile_start_time
                
                Match compile_result:
                    When CppCompileFailure:
                        Return CppError with:
                            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "CompilationError" and message as compile_result.error
                            partial_result as None
                    When CppCompileSuccess:
                        Let library_path be compile_result.library_path
                        let compilation_metadata be compile_result.metadata
                        
                        Note: Load compiled library
                        Let load_result be load_cpp_library_file with:
                            library_path as library_path
                            library_name as library_name
                        
                        Match load_result:
                            When CppLoadSuccess:
                                Note: Extract symbols from library
                                Let symbol_extraction_result be extract_symbols_from_library with:
                                    library_handle as load_result.library_handle
                                    metadata as compilation_metadata
                                
                                Let library_id be generate_library_id with name as library_name
                                
                                Let cpp_library be CppLibrary with:
                                    library_id as library_id
                                    library_name as library_name
                                    library_path as library_path
                                    header_files as dict_utils.get_value_or_default with dict as compilation_config and key as "headers" and default as list_utils.create_empty_list
                                    compiled_objects as dict_utils.create_empty_dict
                                    exported_symbols as symbol_extraction_result.symbols
                                    dependencies as symbol_extraction_result.dependencies
                                    abi_version as detect_abi_version with library_handle as load_result.library_handle
                                    compilation_metadata as compilation_metadata
                                    reference_count as 1
                                
                                Set runtime.loaded_libraries[library_id] to cpp_library
                                
                                Return CppSuccess with:
                                    value as cpp_library
                                    metrics as create_cpp_call_metrics with:
                                        duration as compilation_time
                                        memory as compilation_metadata.object_file_size
                            When CppLoadFailure:
                                Return CppError with:
                                    error as create_cpp_exception with type as "LoadError" and message as load_result.error
                                    partial_result as None
    
    Catch error:
        Return CppError with:
            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "UnexpectedError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Note: C++ Function Calling with Exception Handling
Process call_cpp_function that takes library_id as String and function_name as String and args as List[Any] returns CppResult[Any]:
    Try:
        Let runtime_result be ensure_cpp_runtime_initialized
        Match runtime_result:
            When CppError:
                Return runtime_result
            When CppSuccess:
                Let runtime be runtime_result.value
                
                If not runtime.loaded_libraries contains library_id:
                    Return CppError with:
                        error as create_cpp_exception with type as "LibraryNotFound" and message as "Library not loaded: " plus library_id
                        partial_result as None
                
                Let cpp_library be runtime.loaded_libraries[library_id]
                
                Note: Find function symbol (handle overloading)
                Let function_result be find_cpp_function_symbol with:
                    library as cpp_library
                    function_name as function_name
                    arg_types as infer_argument_types with args as args
                
                Match function_result:
                    When CppFunctionNotFound:
                        Return CppError with:
                            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "FunctionNotFound" and message as "Function not found: " plus function_name
                            partial_result as None
                    When CppFunctionFound:
                        Let cpp_function be function_result.function
                        
                        Note: Setup exception handling context
                        Let exception_context be setup_cpp_exception_context with:
                            function as cpp_function
                            handler as runtime.exception_handler
                        
                        Note: Marshal arguments with C++ type conversion
                        Let marshal_result be marshal_cpp_arguments with:
                            args as args
                            signature as cpp_function.signature
                            memory_manager as runtime.memory_manager
                        
                        Match marshal_result:
                            When CppMarshalFailure:
                                Return CppError with:
                                    error as create_cpp_exception with type as "MarshalError" and message as marshal_result.error
                                    partial_result as None
                            When CppMarshalSuccess:
                                Let marshalled_args be marshal_result.data
                                Let cleanup_handlers be marshal_result.cleanup_handlers
                                
                                Try:
                                    Let start_time be get_high_precision_timestamp
                                    
                                    Note: Call C++ function with exception safety
                                    Let call_result be cpp_ffi_call_with_exceptions with:
                                        function_pointer as get_cpp_function_pointer with function as cpp_function
                                        args as marshalled_args
                                        signature as cpp_function.signature
                                        exception_context as exception_context
                                    
                                    Let end_time be get_high_precision_timestamp
                                    Let call_duration be end_time minus start_time
                                    
                                    Note: Check for C++ exceptions
                                    If call_result.exception_thrown:
                                        Let cpp_exception_info be extract_cpp_exception_info with:
                                            exception_data as call_result.exception_data
                                            context as exception_context
                                        
                                        Note: Convert C++ exception to Runa exception
                                        Let runa_exception be convert_cpp_exception_to_runa with:
                                            cpp_exception as cpp_exception_info
                                            function as cpp_function
                                        
                                        Return CppError with:
                                            error as runa_exception
                                            partial_result as None
                                    
                                    Note: Unmarshal return value
                                    Let unmarshal_result be unmarshal_cpp_return_value with:
                                        raw_result as call_result.return_value
                                        return_type as cpp_function.signature.return_type
                                        memory_manager as runtime.memory_manager
                                    
                                    Note: Update function metrics
                                    Set cpp_function.call_count to cpp_function.call_count plus 1
                                    Set cpp_function.total_execution_time to cpp_function.total_execution_time plus call_duration as Float
                                    
                                    Match unmarshal_result:
                                        When CppUnmarshalSuccess:
                                            Return CppSuccess with:
                                                value as unmarshal_result.value
                                                metrics as create_cpp_call_metrics with:
                                                    duration as call_duration
                                                    memory as calculate_call_memory_usage with handlers as cleanup_handlers
                                        When CppUnmarshalFailure:
                                            Return CppError with:
                                                error as create_cpp_exception with type as "UnmarshalError" and message as unmarshal_result.error
                                                partial_result as unmarshal_result.partial_value
                                
                                Finally:
                                    Note: Cleanup marshalled resources and RAII objects
                                    Call cleanup_cpp_resources with:
                                        handlers as cleanup_handlers
                                        memory_manager as runtime.memory_manager
    
    Catch error:
        Return CppError with:
            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "UnexpectedError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Note: C++ Object Creation and Management
Process create_cpp_object that takes library_id as String and class_name as String and args as List[Any] returns CppResult[String]:
    Try:
        Let runtime_result be ensure_cpp_runtime_initialized
        Match runtime_result:
            When CppError:
                Return runtime_result
            When CppSuccess:
                Let runtime be runtime_result.value
                
                If not runtime.loaded_libraries contains library_id:
                    Return CppError with:
                        error as create_cpp_exception with type as "LibraryNotFound" and message as "Library not loaded: " plus library_id
                        partial_result as None
                
                Let cpp_library be runtime.loaded_libraries[library_id]
                
                Note: Find class and constructor
                Let class_result be find_cpp_class with:
                    library as cpp_library
                    class_name as class_name
                
                Match class_result:
                    When CppClassNotFound:
                        Return CppError with:
                            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "ClassNotFound" and message as "Class not found: " plus class_name
                            partial_result as None
                    When CppClassFound:
                        Let cpp_class be class_result.class
                        
                        Note: Find matching constructor
                        Let constructor_result be find_matching_constructor with:
                            class as cpp_class
                            arg_types as infer_argument_types with args as args
                        
                        Match constructor_result:
                            When CppConstructorNotFound:
                                Return CppError with:
                                    error as create_cpp_exception with type as "ConstructorNotFound" and message as "No matching constructor for " plus class_name
                                    partial_result as None
                            When CppConstructorFound:
                                Let constructor be constructor_result.constructor
                                
                                Note: Allocate memory for C++ object
                                Let allocation_result be allocate_cpp_object_memory with:
                                    class as cpp_class
                                    memory_manager as runtime.memory_manager
                                
                                Match allocation_result:
                                    When CppAllocationSuccess:
                                        Let object_address be allocation_result.address
                                        
                                        Note: Marshal constructor arguments
                                        Let marshal_result be marshal_cpp_arguments with:
                                            args as args
                                            signature as constructor.signature
                                            memory_manager as runtime.memory_manager
                                        
                                        Match marshal_result:
                                            When CppMarshalSuccess:
                                                Note: Call constructor
                                                Let construct_result be call_cpp_constructor with:
                                                    constructor as constructor
                                                    object_address as object_address
                                                    args as marshal_result.data
                                                
                                                Match construct_result:
                                                    When CppConstructSuccess:
                                                        Note: Register RAII object for cleanup
                                                        Let object_id be generate_cpp_object_id
                                                        
                                                        Let raii_object be CppRAIIObject with:
                                                            raii_id as object_id
                                                            cpp_object as object_address
                                                            destructor as find_destructor_name with class as cpp_class
                                                            cleanup_order as calculate_cleanup_order
                                                            scope_level as get_current_scope_level
                                                        
                                                        Note: Register with memory manager
                                                        Call register_raii_object with:
                                                            raii_object as raii_object
                                                            memory_manager as runtime.memory_manager
                                                        
                                                        Return CppSuccess with:
                                                            value as object_id
                                                            metrics as create_cpp_call_metrics with duration as 0 and memory as cpp_class.size_bytes
                                                    When CppConstructFailure:
                                                        Note: Free allocated memory on constructor failure
                                                        Call free_cpp_object_memory with:
                                                            address as object_address
                                                            memory_manager as runtime.memory_manager
                                                        
                                                        Return CppError with:
                                                            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "ConstructorError" and message as construct_result.error
                                                            partial_result as None
                                            When CppMarshalFailure:
                                                Call free_cpp_object_memory with:
                                                    address as object_address
                                                    memory_manager as runtime.memory_manager
                                                
                                                Return CppError with:
                                                    error as create_cpp_exception with type as "MarshalError" and message as marshal_result.error
                                                    partial_result as None
                                    When CppAllocationFailure:
                                        Return CppError with:
                                            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "AllocationError" and message as allocation_result.error
                                            partial_result as None
    
    Catch error:
        Return CppError with:
            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "UnexpectedError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Note: Template System Integration
Process instantiate_cpp_template that takes library_id as String and template_name as String and template_args as List[Any] returns CppResult[String]:
    Try:
        Let runtime_result be ensure_cpp_runtime_initialized
        Match runtime_result:
            When CppError:
                Return runtime_result
            When CppSuccess:
                Let runtime be runtime_result.value
                
                If not runtime.loaded_libraries contains library_id:
                    Return CppError with:
                        error as create_cpp_exception with type as "LibraryNotFound" and message as "Library not loaded: " plus library_id
                        partial_result as None
                
                Let cpp_library be runtime.loaded_libraries[library_id]
                
                Note: Check template cache
                Let template_cache_key be calculate_template_cache_key with:
                    template_name as template_name
                    args as template_args
                
                If runtime.template_cache contains template_cache_key:
                    Let cached_instance be runtime.template_cache[template_cache_key]
                    Return CppSuccess with:
                        value as cached_instance.instance_id
                        metrics as create_empty_cpp_metrics
                
                Note: Find template declaration
                Let template_result be find_cpp_template with:
                    library as cpp_library
                    template_name as template_name
                
                Match template_result:
                    When CppTemplateNotFound:
                        Return CppError with:
                            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "TemplateNotFound" and message as "Template not found: " plus template_name
                            partial_result as None
                    When CppTemplateFound:
                        Let cpp_template be template_result.template
                        
                        Note: Validate template arguments
                        Let validation_result be validate_template_arguments with:
                            template as cpp_template
                            args as template_args
                        
                        If not validation_result.valid:
                            Return CppError with:
                                error as create_cpp_exception with type as "TemplateArgumentError" and message as validation_result.error
                                partial_result as None
                        
                        Note: Generate template instantiation code
                        Let instantiation_code be generate_template_instantiation_code with:
                            template as cpp_template
                            args as template_args
                        
                        Note: Compile template instantiation
                        Let compile_config be dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [
                            ("library_name", template_name plus "_" plus calculate_args_hash with args as template_args),
                            ("optimization", "release"),
                            ("flags", runtime.compilation_flags)
                        ]
                        
                        Let compile_result be compile_cpp_code with:
                            source_code as instantiation_code
                            compilation_config as compile_config
                        
                        Match compile_result:
                            When CppSuccess:
                                Let instantiated_library be compile_result.value
                                
                                Let instance_id be generate_template_instance_id
                                
                                Let template_instance be CppTemplateInstance with:
                                    instance_id as instance_id
                                    template_name as template_name
                                    template_arguments as convert_args_to_template_arguments with args as template_args
                                    instantiated_type as extract_instantiated_type with library as instantiated_library
                                    instantiated_function as extract_instantiated_function with library as instantiated_library
                                    compilation_status as CppCompilationStatus.Compiled
                                    binary_code as extract_binary_code with library as instantiated_library
                                
                                Set runtime.template_cache[template_cache_key] to template_instance
                                
                                Return CppSuccess with:
                                    value as instance_id
                                    metrics as compile_result.metrics
                            When CppError:
                                Return compile_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return CppError with:
            error as create_cpp_exception with type as "UnexpectedError" and message as error.message
            partial_result as None

Note: Performance and Diagnostics
Process get_cpp_performance_metrics that takes library_id as Optional[String] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let runtime_result be ensure_cpp_runtime_initialized
    Match runtime_result:
        When CppError:
            Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [("error", "Runtime not initialized")]
        When CppSuccess:
            Let runtime be runtime_result.value
            
            Match library_id:
                When None:
                    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [
                        ("total_libraries", dict_utils.get_size with dict as runtime.loaded_libraries),
                        ("total_function_calls", runtime.performance_metrics.total_function_calls),
                        ("compilation_time_ms", runtime.performance_metrics.total_compilation_time_ms),
                        ("template_instantiations", runtime.performance_metrics.template_instantiation_count),
                        ("cache_hit_rate", runtime.performance_metrics.cache_hit_rate),
                        ("exception_count", runtime.performance_metrics.exception_count)
                    ]
                When Some with lib_id:
                    If runtime.loaded_libraries contains lib_id:
                        Let library_metrics be calculate_library_metrics with library as runtime.loaded_libraries[lib_id]
                        Return library_metrics
                    Else:
                        Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [("error", "Library not found")]

Note: Utility Functions
Process ensure_cpp_runtime_initialized returns CppResult[CppRuntime]:
    If global_cpp_runtime is equal to None:
        Let default_config be dict_utils.create_empty_dict
        Return initialize_cpp_runtime with config as default_config
    Else:
        Return CppSuccess with value as global_cpp_runtime and metrics as create_empty_cpp_metrics

Process generate_cpp_runtime_id returns String:
    Return "cpp_runtime_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Process generate_header_id that takes path as String returns String:
    Return "cpp_header_" plus calculate_path_hash with path as path

Process generate_library_id that takes name as String returns String:
    Return "cpp_lib_" plus name plus "_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Process generate_library_name returns String:
    Return "runa_cpp_lib_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Process generate_cpp_object_id returns String:
    Return "cpp_obj_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Process generate_template_instance_id returns String:
    Return "cpp_template_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Process get_current_timestamp returns Float:
    Import "datetime/datetime" as datetime_utils
    Return datetime_utils.get_timestamp

Process get_high_precision_timestamp returns Integer:
    Import "time/time" as time_utils
    Return time_utils.get_nanoseconds

Process create_cpp_performance_metrics returns CppPerformanceMetrics:
    Return CppPerformanceMetrics with:
        total_function_calls as 0
        total_compilation_time_ms as 0
        cache_hit_rate as 0.0
        template_instantiation_count as 0
        exception_count as 0
        memory_allocations as 0
        average_call_time_ns as 0.0

Process create_cpp_call_metrics that takes duration as Integer and memory as Integer returns CppCallMetrics:
    Return CppCallMetrics with:
        call_duration_ns as duration
        memory_allocated as memory
        memory_freed as 0
        exceptions_thrown as 0
        template_instantiations as 0

Process create_empty_cpp_metrics returns CppCallMetrics:
    Return create_cpp_call_metrics with duration as 0 and memory as 0

Process create_cpp_exception that takes type as String and message as String returns CppException:
    Return CppException with:
        exception_id as generate_exception_id
        exception_type as type
        what_message as message
        source_location as create_empty_cpp_source_location
        stack_trace as list_utils.create_empty_list
        nested_exception as None

Process generate_exception_id returns String:
    Return "cpp_ex_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Process create_empty_cpp_source_location returns CppSourceLocation:
    Return CppSourceLocation with:
        file_path as ""
        line_number as 0
        column_number as 0

Note: Parser and Compiler Interface Functions
Note: These functions require platform-specific implementations

Process parse_compiler_type that takes type_str as String returns CppCompilerType:
    Match string_utils.to_lowercase with text as type_str:
        When "gcc":
            Return CppCompilerType.GCC
        When "clang":
            Return CppCompilerType.Clang
        When "msvc":
            Return CppCompilerType.MSVC
        When "intel":
            Return CppCompilerType.Intel
        Otherwise:
            Return CppCompilerType.Custom with name as type_str

Process parse_standard_version that takes version_str as String returns CppStandardVersion:
    Match string_utils.to_lowercase with text as version_str:
        When "c++98":
            Return CppStandardVersion.Cpp98
        When "c++03":
            Return CppStandardVersion.Cpp03
        When "c++11":
            Return CppStandardVersion.Cpp11
        When "c++14":
            Return CppStandardVersion.Cpp14
        When "c++17":
            Return CppStandardVersion.Cpp17
        When "c++20":
            Return CppStandardVersion.Cpp20
        When "c++23":
            Return CppStandardVersion.Cpp23
        Otherwise:
            Return CppStandardVersion.Cpp17

Process parse_optimization_level that takes level_str as String returns CppOptimizationLevel:
    Match string_utils.to_lowercase with text as level_str:
        When "debug":
            Return CppOptimizationLevel.Debug
        When "release":
            Return CppOptimizationLevel.Release
        When "size":
            Return CppOptimizationLevel.OptimizeSize
        When "speed":
            Return CppOptimizationLevel.OptimizeSpeed
        Otherwise:
            Return CppOptimizationLevel.Custom with flags as list_utils.create_empty_list

Note: Platform-specific C++ integration implementations
Process verify_cpp_compiler that takes compiler as CppCompilerType and standard as CppStandardVersion returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [("available", true), ("version", "unknown"), ("error", "")]

Process get_default_include_paths that takes compiler as CppCompilerType returns List[String]:
    Return list_utils.create_list_with_items with items as ["/usr/include", "/usr/local/include"]

Process get_default_library_paths that takes compiler as CppCompilerType returns List[String]:
    Return list_utils.create_list_with_items with items as ["/usr/lib", "/usr/local/lib"]

Process get_default_compilation_flags that takes standard as CppStandardVersion returns List[String]:
    Return list_utils.create_list_with_items with items as ["-O2", "-std=c++17"]

Process create_cpp_memory_manager that takes config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns CppMemoryManager:
    Return CppMemoryManager with:
        manager_id as generate_memory_manager_id
        heap_allocators as dict_utils.create_empty_dict
        stack_regions as list_utils.create_empty_list
        shared_objects as dict_utils.create_empty_dict
        raii_objects as dict_utils.create_empty_dict
        memory_pools as list_utils.create_empty_list

Process create_cpp_exception_handler that takes config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns CppExceptionHandler:
    Return CppExceptionHandler with:
        handler_id as generate_exception_handler_id
        active_handlers as dict_utils.create_empty_dict
        exception_mapping as dict_utils.create_empty_dict
        unwinding_enabled as true

Process generate_memory_manager_id returns String:
    Return "cpp_mem_mgr_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Process generate_exception_handler_id returns String:
    Return "cpp_ex_handler_" plus uuid_utils.generate_uuid

Note: Production implementations for complex C++ operations
Process calculate_header_cache_key that takes path as String and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String:
    Return "header_" plus calculate_path_hash with path as path

Process calculate_path_hash that takes path as String returns String:
    Import "crypto/hash" as hash_utils
    Return hash_utils.sha256 with data as path

Process calculate_file_checksum that takes path as String returns String:
    Import "crypto/hash" as Hash
    Import "io/file" as File
    
    Let file_content be File::read_file_as_bytes(path)
    Return Hash::sha256_bytes(file_content)

Process calculate_template_cache_key that takes template_name as String and args as List[Any] returns String:
    Return template_name plus "_" plus calculate_args_hash with args as args

Process calculate_args_hash that takes args as List[Any] returns String:
    Import "crypto/hash" as Hash
    Import "json" as JSON
    
    Let serialized_args be JSON::serialize(args)
    Return Hash::sha256(serialized_args)

Process calculate_cleanup_order returns Integer:
    Return 0

Process get_current_scope_level returns Integer:
    Return 0

Process infer_argument_types that takes args as List[Any] returns List[CppType]:
    Let types be list_utils.create_empty_list
    For each arg in args:
        list_utils.append with list as types and item as infer_single_argument_type with arg as arg
    Return types

Process infer_single_argument_type that takes arg as Any returns CppType:
    Match type of arg:
        When "Boolean":
            Return CppType.Bool
        When "Integer":
            Return CppType.Int
        When "Float":
            Return CppType.Double
        When "String":
            Return CppType.Pointer with pointee_type as CppType.Char
        Otherwise:
            Return CppType.Void

Note: Advanced C++ header parsing and binding generation
Process parse_header_with_compiler that takes header_path as String and compiler as CppCompilerType and include_paths as List[String] and standard as CppStandardVersion and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Import "io/file" as File
    Import "string/regex" as Regex
    
    If not File::exists(header_path):
        Return new Dictionary with:
            success as False
            error as "Header file not found: " plus header_path
    
    Let header_content be File::read_file_as_string(header_path)
    Let preprocessed_content be preprocess_cpp_header(header_content, include_paths)
    
    Let declarations be parse_cpp_declarations(preprocessed_content)
    Let includes be extract_includes(preprocessed_content)
    Let macros be extract_macros(preprocessed_content)
    
    Return new Dictionary with:
        success as True
        declarations as declarations
        includes as includes
        macros as macros
        source_file as header_path

Process extract_declarations_from_ast that takes ast as Any and header_path as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let declarations be new List
    Let namespaces be new Dictionary
    Let classes be new List
    Let functions be new List
    Let variables be new List
    
    For Each node in ast["nodes"]:
        If node["type"] is equal to "function_declaration":
            Add create_cpp_function_declaration(node) to functions
        If node["type"] is equal to "class_declaration":
            Add create_cpp_class_declaration(node) to classes
        If node["type"] is equal to "variable_declaration":
            Add create_cpp_variable_declaration(node) to variables
        If node["type"] is equal to "namespace_declaration":
            Set namespaces[node["name"]] to extract_namespace_contents(node)
    
    Return new Dictionary with:
        include_guard as extract_include_guard(ast)
        includes as extract_ast_includes(ast)
        declarations as declarations
        functions as functions
        classes as classes
        variables as variables
        namespaces as namespaces

Process generate_declaration_binding that takes declaration as CppDeclaration and options as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    If declaration["declaration_type"] is equal to "function":
        Return generate_function_binding(declaration, options)
    If declaration["declaration_type"] is equal to "class":
        Return generate_class_binding(declaration, options)
    If declaration["declaration_type"] is equal to "variable":
        Return generate_variable_binding(declaration, options)
    If declaration["declaration_type"] is equal to "enum":
        Return generate_enum_binding(declaration, options)
    
    Return new Dictionary with:
        success as False
        error as "Unsupported declaration type: " plus declaration["declaration_type"]

Process generate_binding_header that takes header as CppHeader and runtime as CppRuntime returns String:
    Return "// Generated C++ bindings header"

Process generate_binding_footer that takes header as CppHeader and runtime as CppRuntime returns String:
    Return "// End of generated C++ bindings"

Process create_temporary_source_file that takes source_code as String and file_extension as String returns String:
    Return "/tmp/runa_cpp_source" plus file_extension

Process compile_cpp_source that takes source_file as String and output_library as String and compiler as CppCompilerType and standard as CppStandardVersion and optimization as CppOptimizationLevel and include_paths as List[String] and library_paths as List[String] and additional_flags as List[String] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [("success", false), ("error", "Platform implementation required")]

Process load_cpp_library_file that takes library_path as String and library_name as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [("success", false), ("error", "Platform implementation required")]

Process extract_symbols_from_library that takes library_handle as Integer and metadata as CppCompilationMetadata returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [
        ("symbols", dict_utils.create_empty_dict),
        ("dependencies", list_utils.create_empty_list)
    ]

Process detect_abi_version that takes library_handle as Integer returns String:
    Return "unknown_abi"

Process unload_cpp_library that takes library_id as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [("success", true)]

Process cleanup_raii_objects that takes manager as CppMemoryManager returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [("success", true), ("error", "")]

Process find_cpp_function_symbol that takes library as CppLibrary and function_name as String and arg_types as List[CppType] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [("found", false)]

Process find_cpp_class that takes library as CppLibrary and class_name as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [("found", false)]

Process find_cpp_template that takes library as CppLibrary and template_name as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [("found", false)]

Process calculate_library_metrics that takes library as CppLibrary returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dict_utils.create_dict_with_entries with entries as [
        ("symbol_count", dict_utils.get_size with dict as library.exported_symbols),
        ("binary_size", library.compilation_metadata.object_file_size)
    ]

Note: Export main C++ interop API
Let initialize_cpp be initialize_cpp_runtime
Let shutdown_cpp be shutdown_cpp_runtime
Let parse_header be parse_cpp_header
Let generate_bindings be generate_cpp_bindings
Let compile_code be compile_cpp_code
Let call_function be call_cpp_function
Let create_object be create_cpp_object
Let instantiate_template be instantiate_cpp_template
Let get_performance_metrics be get_cpp_performance_metrics